Savannah Cement has set sights on deals in regional infrastructure projects to grow its market share. The cement maker, which started operations in 2012, supplies up to 2,500 tonnes of cement monthly at the Sh8.5 billion Outer Ring Road expansion project. &ldquo;The firm has been actively pursuing supply opportunities to local and regional infrastructure development projects successfully riding on the firm&rsquo;s consistent product quality,&rdquo; Savannah Cement managing director Ronald Ndegwa said. He was speaking during a visit to Outer Ring Road Construction Contractor Sinohydro Corporation, and paving blocks manufacturer KenBro in Nairobi. &ldquo;We have had consistent quality and efficient service delivery,&rdquo; Sinohydro chief engineer Zhou Chong said.